To anyone going through breakup. Trust me time heals , it does
Things not to do after breakup
1. No contact ❌ no ladies and gentlemen no
2. If they live in neighbourhood (don't look at their houses and avoid going to terrace)
3. No contact with their friends as well 
4. Unfollow , block forever 
Ik these things are hard but trust me you people will be super fine after a while. May god bless everyone ❤❤❤

snippet.textDisplay:
Some songs don’t just play in your ears—they settle in your heart.
Faasle isn’t just about distance, it's about the silence between words, the ache in waiting, and the beauty in love that stays even when people don’t.
Kaavish and Quratulain’s voices carry pain so gracefully, it feels like they’re singing the story we all are too scared to tell.
Thank you for reminding us that even separation can be beautiful when felt deeply♥️

snippet.textDisplay:
---

Before the age of 20, listening to this kind of music used to feel strange — back then, we liked a completely different kind of music.
But now, as life moves beyond 25, this music finally makes sense.

A line that was said almost six or seven years ago — "Hue faaslay, jhoothay silsilay, toote hue dil jayein kahaan" —
It's not just a line anymore. It’s a complete summary of our feelings, our emotions.
It touches the heart in a way that’s hard to explain.

In fact, it’s not just this one line — the entire song  is overflowing with emotion.
And now, I truly don’t know — where do broken hearts go?
Is this world even made for those with broken hearts?


---🙂🤍
